// ⚠️  REQUIRED FOR FCM PUSH NOTIFICATIONS
//
// To enable incoming VoIP call notifications when the app is closed:
//
//  1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com/
//  2. Create a project (or use an existing one)
//  3. Click "Add app" → Android
//  4. Package name: com.voiceguard
//  5. Download google-services.json
//  6. Place it at:  voiceguard/app/android/app/google-services.json
//     (same folder as this placeholder file)
//  7. Delete this placeholder file
//
// Signaling server (for sending pushes):
//  1. In Firebase Console → Project Settings → Service Accounts
//  2. Click "Generate new private key" → download JSON
//  3. Place it at:  voiceguard/server/firebase-service-account.json
//  4. Set env var:  GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=./firebase-service-account.json
//     (add to your server/.env file)
//
// The app works WITHOUT Firebase — VoIP calls simply require the app to be
// open on the callee's phone. With Firebase, calls wake the app from any state.
